article.headline: Portland St. 78, N. Arizona 66
article.story: PORTLAND, Ore. -- Dominic Waters scored 16 points and connected on all four of his 3-point attempts to lead Portland State to a 78-66 win over Northern Arizona on Thursday night. Jeremiah Dominguez had a double-double of 15 points and 11 assists for the Vikings (16-7, 7-3 Big Sky Conference), who beat Northern Arizona for the sixth straight time. Julius Thomas and Andre Murray each chipped in 12 points for Portland State. Cameron Jones led Northern Arizona (6-15, 3-7 Big Sky) with 15 points and Matt Johnson had 12 points for the Lumberjacks. The Vikings led 47-35 early in the second half after Dominguez hit a 3-pointer with 17 minutes remaining in the game and were never challenged the rest of the way.
